Likely to Take the PHR or SPHR? Three Exam Preparation Tips



Getting prepared to take the PHR or SPHR certification exam can certainly appear to be a massive task to tackle. However, if you have the combination of education and experience requirements necessary to sit for the test of your liking and you're simply willing to devote a lot of time to studying and honing your test preparation skills, earning a PHR or SPHR credential is not impossible. Here are a few tips - from somebody who has been teaching certification preparation classes for quite some time - that you may find to be helpful as you begin the process of getting prepared to earn professional certification through HRCI.

Three PHR/SPHR Exam Preparation Tips

1. Use the SHRM Learning System

While the SHRM Learning system is not inexpensive, it is truly the best resource for mastering the material that is covered around the PHR and SPHR preparation exam. There are other books and study materials available, however they weren't compiled by exactly the same organization that produces the test you're taking. It only makes sense to go directly to the origin for your exam preparation materials. All you need to know to master the knowledge requirements for the test is in the system.

The only reason you need to even consider seeking study material beyond the SHRM Learning System would be if you had truly mastered everything in the machine, including the thought processes behind arriving at the best answers for each among the sample questions provide in the books and also the online materials, in addition to every other supplemental materials available through HRCI.

