2. Perfect Your Test Taking Skills

While mastering the data contained in the HRCI body of data is an integral part of having ready to sit for this exam, it is just on bit of what you need to caused by get ready. Honing your test taking skills - specific to this exam - is a vital bit of the test preparation process. Use the test questions including within the learning system books along with the online studying being an integral part of your studying process.

Don't just rely on them to test your knowledge, but focus on the procedure for thinking through what is being asked, eliminating wrong answers to narrow down the options and applying your professional making decisions and critical thinking skills to reach the right response. Should you miss an issue, don't just chalk it up to creating a poor decision and move on. Return through the materials to discover why another answer was better so you end up with a deeper understanding of the question and also the answer.

3. Exceed Memorizing

The misguided belief that memorizing information and focus questions is sufficient for exam preparation is probably the biggest misconception that exists about PHR and SPHR exam preparation. You simply cannot memorize the right path into earning a PHR or SPHR certification. You will not see the same test questions you accustomed to study on the exam itself. The objective of the sample questions is to educate you on how to consider exam questions, not to provide you with what to memorize. You'll have to do a lot of memorizing to prepare for that exam, but that is insufficient.

You can't become a certified HR professional based simply in your knowledge of industry terminology and definitions or just being in a position to state the end result of landmark law suits. To be able to earn a PHR or SPHR certification, you must be able to take the information and data that a true human resource professional will need and put it on effectively to real-world situations using high level critical thinking skills in order to earn your certification.